				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6454589/scp-3687#post-3878084</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 18 Jul 2018 18:32:01 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Moti5stars</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2940595</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>The concept is good for an SCP article. I've seen little mistakes, such as:</p> <blockquote> <p>Witnesses to the SCP-3687 were treated with class-B amnestics&#8230;</p> </blockquote> <p>Shouldn't this be &quot;Witnesses to SCP-3687&#8230;&quot; or &quot;Witnesses to the incident&#8230;&quot;?</p> <p>But it's original and well-thought. +1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
